  <Section padding="large" theme="brand" id="accordion">
    <Layout variant="sticky-left" verticalAlign="start">
      <Col slot="col1">
        <Heading variant="eyebrow" class="u-margin-bottom-3">Accordion</Heading>
        <Heading tag="h2" variant="h1" balance accent>
          Common questions, <strong>answered</strong>
        </Heading>
        <Text variant="regular">
          The Accordion and AccordionItem components animate with GSAP for
          smooth height transitions. Set openByDefault to pre-expand an item on
          load.
        </Text>
        <div class="u-button-wrapper">
          <Button href="/style-guide" ariaLabel="View style guide"
            >View style guide</Button
          >
        </div>
      </Col>

      <Accordion docs="" slot="col2" openByDefault={1}>
        <AccordionItem question="What is the design system?">
          <Text>
            A structured CSS and component system. It
            uses CSS custom properties, a u- utility class layer, and an Astro
            component layer to give you total design control with fast
            development speed.
          </Text>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="How do I use the Section component?">
          <Text>
            Wrap any page section in a Section component and pass a theme
            (light, dark, or brand), a padding size, and optionally a container
            width. The component handles spacing tokens and theme cascading
            automatically.
          </Text>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="Can I mix layout variants on the same page?">
          <Text>
            Yes. Each Layout instance is fully independent. Mix columns for
            balanced sections, breakout for accent panels, and sticky-left for
            FAQ or feature-detail patterns all on the same page.
          </Text>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem
          question="Is JavaScript required for components to work?"
        >
          <Text>
            Accordion and Slider require GSAP and Swiper v8 respectively — both
            are loaded via CDN. The Modal uses a native dialog element with a
            lightweight controller. All other components are pure HTML and CSS.
          </Text>
        </AccordionItem>

        <AccordionItem question="How do I trigger a modal from a button?">
          <Text>
            Add data-modal-trigger="your-id" to any button or link. Render a
            Modal with id="your-id" anywhere on the page — the JS controller
            wires them up automatically on DOMContentLoaded.
          </Text>
        </AccordionItem>
      </Accordion>
    </Layout>
  </Section>

